sections.heading: application.The Uniform Electronic Transactions Act applies to any electronic record or electronic signature created, generated, sent, communicated, received, or stored on or after July 13, 2000

sections.text:
86-631.Prospective application.

The Uniform Electronic Transactions Act applies to any electronic record or electronic signature created, generated, sent, communicated, received, or stored on or after July 13, 2000.

SourceLaws 2000, LB 929, § 4;R.S.Supp.,2000, § 86-2104;Laws 2002, LB 1105, § 393.
